import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['state', 'city'])
    state_counts = data.groupby('state')['city'].count().reset_index()
    state_counts = state_counts.sort_values(by='city', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="state", y="city", data=state_counts)
    ax.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Count of Cities')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cities across different states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="darkgrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x="city", data=data, order=data['city'].value_counts().index)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90, ha="right")
    plt.title('What is the most common city in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.axvline(data['lon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')

    plt.title('What is the distribution of cities across different longitude values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
